						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 777 (?).</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [7]00, Durmati, Chaitra, Amāvāsyā, [Satur]day.</hi> If the Śaka year was current, the details given correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 777, April 12,</hi> when the cyclic year was Piṅgaḷa and not Durmati. In the cyclic year Durmati corresponding to Śaka 703 (781 A.D.), the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> fell on March 29, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription records the death of an individual in a fight It refers to Kanna and a <hi rend="italic">perggaḍe.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
